## Package Manager

**Always use pnpm for package management in this project.**

- Use `pnpm install` instead of `npm install` or `yarn install`
- Use `pnpm add <package>` instead of `npm install <package>`
- Use `pnpm remove <package>` instead of `npm uninstall <package>`
- Use `pnpm run <script>` instead of `npm run <script>`
- This project uses pnpm workspaces (see `pnpm-workspace.yaml`)

## Scripts

- Use `pnpm run format` for code formatting
- Use `pnpm run lint` for linting
- Use `pnpm run build` for building the project
- Use `pnpm run dev` for development server (if available)

When suggesting or running commands, always use pnpm commands rather than npm or yarn equivalents.
